<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Notes.</emphasis>
This species was described from 
<specimenCount box="[649,762,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
from “Klein-Asien” and “Astrabad” (
<bibRefCitation author="Seidlitz, G. C. M. von" box="[1187,1346,150,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" pagination="609 - 800" refId="ref23469" refString="Seidlitz, G. C. M. von (1895) Tenebrionidae. In: Kiesenwetter, H. von &amp; Seidlitz, G. C. M. von (Eds.), Naturgeschichte der Insecten Deutschlands. Begonnen von Dr. W. F. Erichson, fortgesetzt von Prof. Dr. H. Schaum, Dr. G. Kraatz, H. v. Kiesenwetter, Julius Weise, Edm. Reitter und Dr. G. Seidlitz. Erste Abteilung Coleoptera. Funfter Band. Erste Halfte. Nicolaische Verlags-Buchhandlung, Berlin, pp. 609 - 800. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8270" type="book chapter" year="1895">Seidlitz, 1895</bibRefCitation>
, p. 707) in the key. 
<bibRefCitation author="Leo, P. &amp; Ruzzante, G." box="[273,556,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" pagination="83 - 89" refId="ref22267" refString="Leo, P. &amp; Ruzzante, G. (2016) Dati nuovi e riassuntivi sui Tenebrionidi dell'isola di Lesbo (Grecia) (Coleoptera Tenebrionidae). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 148, 83 - 89." type="journal article" year="2016">Leo and Ruzzante (2016)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that it is a “mysterious” species, described from these two different localities. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sahlberg, J. R." box="[267,451,223,249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" pagination="1 - 282" refId="ref23309" refString="Sahlberg, J. R. (1913) Coleoptera mediterranea orientalis quae in aegypto, Palestina, Syria, Caramania collegerunt John Sahlberg et unio Saalas. Ofversigt af Finska Vetenskaps-Societetens Forhandlingar, 55, 1 - 282." type="journal article" year="1913">Sahlberg (1913)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter, E." box="[464,623,223,249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref23264" refString="Reitter, E. (1922) Bestimmungstabelle der palaearktischen Helopinae (Col. Tenebrionidae). Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 39, 1 - 44 + 113 - 171. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 2572" type="journal article" year="1922">Reitter (1922)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nabozhenko, M. V. &amp; Lobl, I." box="[679,1013,223,249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" pagination="1802" refId="ref22757" refString="Nabozhenko, M. V. &amp; Lobl, I. (2008) Tribe Helopini Latreille, 1802. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Apollo books, Stenstrup, pp. 241 - 257." type="book chapter" year="2008">Nabozhenko and Löbl (2008)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned different species from the 
<collectingRegion box="[151,320,259,285]" country="Greece" name="Voreio Aigaio" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Aegean region</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nabozhenko, M. V." box="[332,571,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" pagination="1802" refId="ref22635" refString="Nabozhenko, M. V. (2020 b) Tribe Helopini Latreille, 1802. In: Iwan, D. &amp; Lobl, I. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 5. Tenebrionoidea. Leiden, Brill, pp. 314 - 339. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004434998 _ 004" type="book chapter" year="2020">
Nabozhenko (2020 
<emphasis box="[548,562,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">b</emphasis>
)
</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seidlitz" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[649,807,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Euboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corrugosus">
<emphasis box="[649,807,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">E. corrugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for 
<collectingCountry box="[857,939,259,285]" name="Greece" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[951,1031,259,285]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1089,1138,259,285]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Iran</collectingCountry>
. One 
<typeStatus box="[1205,1292,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">syntype</typeStatus>
(male) from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[161,296,295,321]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Asia Minor</collectingCountry>
” was originally mentioned from the collection of G. Kraatz, but it was not found in the Senckenberg Deutsche Entomologische Institut (Müncheberg, 
<collectingCountry box="[700,810,331,357]" name="Germany" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Germany</collectingCountry>
). I studied the second Iranian specimen (designated here as the 
<typeStatus box="[223,328,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">lectotype</typeStatus>
) (
<figureCitation box="[351,417,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1049,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-324@2.[151,1436,1049,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Euboeus corrugosus, lectotype, male, habitus.A = dorsally; B = laterally; C = labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785913" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785913/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), which is conspecific to Medvedev’s 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Medvedev" authorityYear="1977" box="[851,1002,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Probaticus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parthorum">
<emphasis box="[851,1002,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">E. parthorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1018,1085,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[229,1350,530,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-156@3.[226,1361,525,1873]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Euboeus corrugosus, types of E. parthorum, syn. nov., habitus, details of structure. A = male, holotype dorsally; B = label of holotype; C = male, paratype, ventrally; D = female, paratype, dorsally; E = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; F = ditto, dorso-laterally; G = prothoracic hypomeron; H = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; I = spiculum gastrale; J = tegmen, ventrally; K = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; L = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785917/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) also described from Astrabad. Thus, the following new synonymy is proposed: 
<taxonomicName authority="Seidlitz, 1895" authorityName="Seidlitz" authorityYear="1895" box="[724,1109,402,429]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Helops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corrugosus">
<emphasis box="[724,940,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Helops corrugosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Seidlitz, G. C. M. von" box="[950,1109,402,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" pagination="609 - 800" refId="ref23469" refString="Seidlitz, G. C. M. von (1895) Tenebrionidae. In: Kiesenwetter, H. von &amp; Seidlitz, G. C. M. von (Eds.), Naturgeschichte der Insecten Deutschlands. Begonnen von Dr. W. F. Erichson, fortgesetzt von Prof. Dr. H. Schaum, Dr. G. Kraatz, H. v. Kiesenwetter, Julius Weise, Edm. Reitter und Dr. G. Seidlitz. Erste Abteilung Coleoptera. Funfter Band. Erste Halfte. Nicolaische Verlags-Buchhandlung, Berlin, pp. 609 - 800. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8270" type="book chapter" year="1895">Seidlitz, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="G. Medvedev, 1976" authorityName="G. Medvedev" authorityYear="1976" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Probaticus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parthorum" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1146,1399,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Probaticus parthorum</emphasis>
G. 
<bibRefCitation author="Medvedev, G. S." box="[151,341,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" pagination="889 - 902" refId="ref22349" refString="Medvedev, G. S. (1976) New species of darkling beetles (Coleoptera, Tenebrionidae) from Iran. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 55, 889 - 902." type="journal article" year="1976">Medvedev, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[352,455,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[352,455,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
